	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon10.gif" alt="Talking" border="0" />
				<strong>Resettable timers</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#FFFFFF" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>This is a beta release of my resettable timers.  Just a few examples to show how the timers work.  I've used the music player window this time.<br />
<br />
The first one is a tick timer.  It changes color every six seconds.  By adjusting the slider you can set it to match the ticks in your current zone.<br />
<br />
Knowing exactly when a tick ends can be useful for pulling, or for sneaking past a mob without it seeing you.  It can also be useful for short duration spells like Word of Morell.  It's useful to know whether WoM will last for 6.5 seconds or 11.5 seconds... without a tick timer it's hard to predict.<br />
<br />
The next three are 20-minute timers.  I chose 20 minutes because that's the respawn time in Droga.  The idea is that you adjust the timer so the bar is solid white.  Then the red bar slowly drifts across.  When the bar is solid white again, 20 minutes have passed.  I made three of them to show that they can be be set independently, even though all three use the same animation.  I've included an editable field with each one for descriptions.<br />
<br />
The final one is a 6-minute timer.  It's basically the same idea, but a dancing banana-man is riding the red bar.  Adjust it so banana-man is off-screen... he'll dance across the timer and six minutes later he'll be off-screen again.  You can use it to time less than six minutes too... the tick marks show one minute increments.<br />
<br />
I've shrunk the scroll buttons to 15 pixels wide instead of the standard 22 for good reason.  At that size, each pixel movement of the slider has exactly the same movement of the picture: 4 pixels on the ticker and 3 pixels on the timers.<br />
<br />
Enjoy :)</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
