		<!-- message -->
		<div>Ok banana-man was amusing, but now I'm making them more polished.  I've used the music player window again.<br />
<br />
First, I got rid of the arrow buttons and the gutter altogether.  Who needs em anyway, I just slide the thumb.  This looks better, simplifies the xml, and improves the resolution.<br />
<br />
Next I switched from a two-color timer to a one-color timer with a mark.  This reduces the size of the graphics, reduces the size of the xml, and improves resolution again.<br />
<br />
Now my proper two-color timer has a 3-pixel resolution.  A simple two-color timer like my tick timer gets a 2-pixel resolution.  My one-color timer also has a 2-pixel resolution.  The marker on traditional timers has a 1-pixel resolution.<br />
<br />
Finally I imitated some of Arista's graphics for better comparison, and threw in some vertical timers too, to show off.  The circle moves all the way across every 20 minutes, and you can reset it by moving the thumb.<br />
<br />
Does this look good?</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
